caption: The most ridiculously opulent and decadent private home, or Hotel Particulier as the French call it.  It was so hard to get a slot to see it, one has to book well in advance, and with a guided tour, which was all in French!  It didn’t matter, even if o understood what was being said my mind was too busy being blown to concentrate on words!  The history is amazing and as delicious and salacious as one would expect!!!!!  I saw things I’ve never seen anywhere else’s in terms of design and art!
So glad that finally open dates and my paris days coincided! Hard to get access, well worth the wait!

Not an hotel as such, but The Travellers Club, Paris. Which is a private members club. So Google should correct the current entry as misleading. Brilliant of you are entitled to use the club. A wonderful building.
A palace gem on an iconic road
Beautiful gem of Napoléon III architecture which ,ou only can visit in form of a guided tour or as a member of the Travellers Club.
Very interesting museum, try to come with the guide.
Private club where you can go if you're invited by a member some nights. We had dinner there, excellent food & wine, very good service.

Between 1856 and 1866, this residence was built as the home of the most famous of the 19th-century French courtesans (also known as demi-mondes and grandes horizontales), the Parisian Cocotte "la Païva". See wikipedia under La Païva or Hôtel de la Païva for more.
